WEBVTT

00:00:34.722 --> 00:00:38.059
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

00:00:38.143 --> 00:00:39.894
AUTHORIZATION LETTER

00:00:39.978 --> 00:00:41.813
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
HONG JANG-MI

00:00:46.818 --> 00:00:48.486
I am indeed Hong Jang-mi.

00:00:49.112 --> 00:00:51.447
Yes, we've confirmed your name and face,

00:00:51.531 --> 00:00:54.826
but we should be extra careful
with such a large sum of money.

00:00:56.369 --> 00:00:57.203
Just a moment.

00:01:14.387 --> 00:01:15.221
Madam Choi.

00:01:18.600 --> 00:01:20.143
Let's talk in my office.

00:01:43.958 --> 00:01:45.501
My goodness. Nora!

00:01:47.587 --> 00:01:48.838
This is…

00:01:48.922 --> 00:01:51.633
This is exactly why
I didn't want to work here!

00:01:51.716 --> 00:01:54.093
Do you think anyone
in this building welcomes me?

00:01:54.177 --> 00:01:56.596
They're always whispering when I walk by,

00:01:56.679 --> 00:01:58.723
so I can't even get water
or go to the bathroom!

00:02:00.266 --> 00:02:01.100
My poor Nora.

00:02:02.018 --> 00:02:04.437
This place is bringing out a side of you
I've never seen.

00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:05.355
Oh dear.

00:02:16.282 --> 00:02:18.409
Hello, you've reached Song Ju-ran.

00:02:23.665 --> 00:02:24.499
That's correct.

00:02:24.999 --> 00:02:27.293
I can verify Ms. Hong Jang-mi.

00:02:27.877 --> 00:02:29.879
We're in urgent need of those funds,

00:02:29.963 --> 00:02:31.589
so please proceed without delay.

00:02:32.507 --> 00:02:34.467
Yes, ma'am. I understand.

00:02:39.806 --> 00:02:40.890
Did you confirm with her?

00:02:42.267 --> 00:02:44.102
Yes, I did.

00:02:53.861 --> 00:02:56.322
YEOUIDO PIRATES

00:02:57.115 --> 00:02:58.950
EPISODE 11: THE MASKED PIRATE

00:02:59.534 --> 00:03:02.161
CHRISTMAS SUPPLIES MEGA SALE

00:03:07.375 --> 00:03:08.793
{\an8}Why didn't you answer your phone?

00:03:08.876 --> 00:03:10.920
{\an8}I passed out
as soon as I got on the train to Seoul.

00:03:11.004 --> 00:03:12.588
{\an8}Did you get it? Is it done?

00:03:14.090 --> 00:03:15.341
{\an8}Withdrawal complete.

00:03:15.425 --> 00:03:17.427
{\an8}I got it all in checks,
just like you told me to.

00:03:26.853 --> 00:03:28.563
{\an8}You couldn't have
pulled this off without me.

00:03:28.646 --> 00:03:30.523
{\an8}I was sweating bullets earlier.

00:03:31.024 --> 00:03:33.484
{\an8}But still, Ms. Kang
definitely pulled her weight.

00:03:33.568 --> 00:03:36.237
{\an8}She only cooperated
because she didn't exactly know our plan.

00:03:36.946 --> 00:03:38.156
Let's take care of this first.

00:03:38.239 --> 00:03:41.701
They could stop payment on these checks,
so we need to cash them quickly.

00:03:41.784 --> 00:03:42.618
Let's go.

00:03:52.378 --> 00:03:54.547
ALWAYS READY TO HELP OUR CLIENTS
LIKE WE'RE FAMILY

00:03:54.630 --> 00:03:56.007
IOK DEVELOPMENT OFFICE

00:03:59.761 --> 00:04:01.471
How did you find out about this place?

00:04:01.971 --> 00:04:03.014
You sure we'll be okay?

00:04:03.097 --> 00:04:04.682
Of course we'll be okay.

00:04:04.766 --> 00:04:07.268
The Bank of Korea
is right across the street.

00:04:08.061 --> 00:04:10.813
Sometimes what's closest
is the hardest to notice.

00:04:31.042 --> 00:04:33.419
CASHIER'S CHECK
10 MILLION WON

00:04:45.515 --> 00:04:46.641
The service fee is 20%.

00:04:48.893 --> 00:04:51.437
It's supposed to be 15%.
I already checked.

00:04:52.355 --> 00:04:54.649
It's 20%
with the late-night surcharge included.

00:04:57.819 --> 00:04:58.653
Eighteen…

00:05:00.446 --> 00:05:01.531
percent.

00:05:02.490 --> 00:05:03.991
You really are something else.

00:05:04.075 --> 00:05:05.618
Look at you trying to save every penny.

00:05:05.701 --> 00:05:07.995
I'm not just doing this
for my own sake, am I?

00:05:16.337 --> 00:05:18.131
Would that be enough to change your mind?

00:05:18.673 --> 00:05:21.384
Let's settle on 17%
with a bulk discount included.

00:05:48.035 --> 00:05:50.496
I've stolen my fair share,
but I never felt butterflies like this.

00:05:50.580 --> 00:05:51.956
I feel angry.

00:05:52.039 --> 00:05:54.458
Look how much
these greedy bastards have stashed away.

00:05:55.042 --> 00:05:57.837
This isn't even a tenth
of Chairman Kang's slush fund.

00:06:06.137 --> 00:06:07.180
It's dirty money.

00:06:07.263 --> 00:06:09.390
When I was a teller,
I used to get so annoyed

00:06:09.473 --> 00:06:11.684
when my fingers got irritated
from handling so much cash.

00:06:11.767 --> 00:06:12.602
Why?

00:06:12.685 --> 00:06:14.937
Because all that cash I touched
was never mine.

00:06:16.189 --> 00:06:17.732
But now,

00:06:19.233 --> 00:06:22.195
I don't think I'd mind
having all ten fingers irritated.

00:06:22.820 --> 00:06:24.280
I want to count every single bill.

00:06:24.363 --> 00:06:26.324
Remember, this still isn't your money.

00:06:27.366 --> 00:06:28.284
I know that.

00:06:29.702 --> 00:06:30.536
Oh right.

00:06:30.620 --> 00:06:32.872
Did I tell you
that Nora got caught by the president

00:06:32.955 --> 00:06:34.332
while filling in for you today?

00:06:34.415 --> 00:06:35.249
She did?

00:06:35.333 --> 00:06:36.792
Why are you only telling me this now?

00:06:57.104 --> 00:06:58.981
I need an explanation
for yesterday's incident

00:06:59.065 --> 00:07:00.608
from the one responsible, Ms. Hong.

00:07:00.691 --> 00:07:04.195
Mr. Cha has banned days off
since the restructuring.

00:07:04.779 --> 00:07:06.530
That's why I helped her out.

00:07:06.614 --> 00:07:08.324
Why did you need to take your day off?

00:07:10.076 --> 00:07:11.786
It was for personal reasons.

00:07:11.869 --> 00:07:13.955
As the guardian
of her hospitalized roommate--

00:07:14.038 --> 00:07:15.748
I want you to speak for yourself.

00:07:16.499 --> 00:07:19.126
You should know
that repeated unexcused absences

00:07:19.835 --> 00:07:21.087
may be grounds for termination.

00:07:29.262 --> 00:07:31.639
I was indeed absent without prior approval

00:07:31.722 --> 00:07:35.142
and foolishly attempted to rectify it
by involving a third party.

00:07:35.226 --> 00:07:37.520
I will make sure this never happens again,

00:07:37.603 --> 00:07:38.563
and I'll be more mindful.

00:07:38.646 --> 00:07:40.273
We'll be more mindful.

00:07:49.615 --> 00:07:50.449
You may leave.

00:08:13.097 --> 00:08:16.642
President Shin just let us go
because you're such a smooth talker.

00:08:16.726 --> 00:08:20.396
He just couldn't grill us further
because you were there, Ms. Kang.

00:08:22.440 --> 00:08:24.275
I'll do even better next time.

00:08:24.358 --> 00:08:25.985
Thank you for your help.

00:08:27.987 --> 00:08:29.739
This is the address where Bom is.

00:08:30.239 --> 00:08:31.532
It's my parents' place.

00:08:35.703 --> 00:08:37.580
1001 SINJANG-DONG, YEOGOK-GU, INCHEON

00:08:50.676 --> 00:08:53.512
When I show up to work
dressed like this as Kang Nora,

00:08:53.596 --> 00:08:55.264
people find me intimidating.

00:08:55.348 --> 00:08:57.391
But the moment
I put the uniform back on yesterday,

00:08:57.475 --> 00:08:59.935
they treated me just as badly
as when I was Kang Eun-joo.

00:09:01.395 --> 00:09:03.731
But I've been the same person
all this time.

00:09:05.149 --> 00:09:08.611
I wondered if this was
how you'd been feeling too.

00:09:11.656 --> 00:09:14.158
We should have lunch
with Queen Bee sometime.

00:09:14.742 --> 00:09:15.910
We'll go to that place we used to--

00:09:15.993 --> 00:09:16.869
The burger place!

00:09:17.453 --> 00:09:18.704
I'd love to.

00:09:18.788 --> 00:09:19.622
Totally.

00:09:21.290 --> 00:09:22.124
I'll get going then.

00:09:38.724 --> 00:09:40.351
"Ullala Chicken"?

00:09:42.687 --> 00:09:43.562
This is so good.

00:09:43.646 --> 00:09:45.022
ULLALA CHICKEN

00:09:45.106 --> 00:09:46.816
Is this the same delicious fried chicken

00:09:47.441 --> 00:09:48.943
that Queen Bee treated us to last time?

00:09:49.026 --> 00:09:51.362
HONG KEUM-BO'S
BIRTHDAY PARTY INVITATION

00:09:51.445 --> 00:09:53.155
Did you fold this star, Bom?

00:09:56.701 --> 00:09:58.828
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

00:09:59.578 --> 00:10:00.788
Auntie!

00:10:01.914 --> 00:10:03.082
Bom!

00:10:04.125 --> 00:10:05.292
How have you been?

00:10:05.835 --> 00:10:08.963
Oh my gosh. I missed you so much!

00:10:12.299 --> 00:10:13.384
Hello.

00:10:17.304 --> 00:10:19.598
I missed you so much.

00:10:19.682 --> 00:10:20.725
Have you been well?

00:10:24.186 --> 00:10:25.020
Here we go.

00:10:25.104 --> 00:10:27.148
Open up.

00:10:28.899 --> 00:10:30.693
Give me one too.

00:10:31.986 --> 00:10:33.362
Open up.

00:10:35.573 --> 00:10:36.907
It's so good.

00:10:41.996 --> 00:10:44.665
Why didn't you say goodbye
before you left?

00:10:44.749 --> 00:10:45.791
Sorry.

00:10:46.459 --> 00:10:49.170
I had to move in with my mom and dad
all of a sudden.

00:10:49.253 --> 00:10:50.963
With your mom and dad?

00:10:53.424 --> 00:10:54.550
Lucky you.

00:10:57.595 --> 00:10:59.180
It's okay.

00:10:59.263 --> 00:11:02.725
I live with Grandma and Grandpa here.

00:11:03.267 --> 00:11:06.812
Even today,
Grandma and I went to see Mommy.

00:11:08.397 --> 00:11:09.565
Here we go.

00:11:12.818 --> 00:11:14.278
Enjoy.

00:11:14.361 --> 00:11:15.988
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:11:18.824 --> 00:11:19.658
Bom.

00:11:20.409 --> 00:11:21.869
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

00:11:23.746 --> 00:11:25.623
So she used to live with Keum-bo?

00:11:26.415 --> 00:11:28.667
Man, she sure smells of money.

00:11:29.251 --> 00:11:30.669
Be quiet.

00:11:31.337 --> 00:11:33.047
- It's good.
- It's good!

00:11:35.966 --> 00:11:36.884
Eat up.

00:11:43.891 --> 00:11:45.518
Sir, I'm here to pick up…

00:11:49.438 --> 00:11:50.606
FULL-SERVICE SHOE REPAIR

00:11:50.689 --> 00:11:53.484
After you went silent, I even went to
Seoul Station to look for you,

00:11:53.567 --> 00:11:54.902
afraid that you'd become homeless.

00:11:58.155 --> 00:12:00.324
I delayed processing your resignation.

00:12:00.908 --> 00:12:02.409
You still haven't processed it?

00:12:03.369 --> 00:12:04.370
Why you little…

00:12:04.453 --> 00:12:06.580
I clearly did it for your sake.

00:12:09.833 --> 00:12:11.752
Remember the 24 billion won
in Hong Jang-mi's accounts?

00:12:12.503 --> 00:12:14.255
I withdrew everything in checks,
and they're being cashed.

00:12:17.883 --> 00:12:19.552
Have you lost your damn mind?

00:12:19.635 --> 00:12:21.971
It's not like
I can claim that money anyway,

00:12:22.555 --> 00:12:24.723
so I'm going to buy up
all the Hanmin stocks.

00:12:26.433 --> 00:12:27.810
I'll buy the company with the slush fund.

00:12:27.893 --> 00:12:30.396
I sent you undercover
to catch the big crook,

00:12:30.479 --> 00:12:31.730
and now you'll become one yourself?

00:12:31.814 --> 00:12:32.815
Then what?

00:12:32.898 --> 00:12:35.067
Should I just let
those foreign invaders loot it all?

00:12:36.360 --> 00:12:38.696
DK Ventures isn't looking
to invest in Hanmin,

00:12:38.779 --> 00:12:41.073
but to stage a hostile takeover
of its management rights.

00:12:41.949 --> 00:12:43.784
It's true that Chairman Kang
is a jerk and all,

00:12:43.867 --> 00:12:45.869
but we can't lose the company to them.

00:12:51.166 --> 00:12:54.628
You shouldn't underestimate
DK Ventures like that.

00:12:54.712 --> 00:12:56.297
I looked into them,

00:12:56.380 --> 00:12:59.133
and it turns out they've swept through
Southeast Asia's corporate world

00:12:59.216 --> 00:13:00.634
since the start of the year.

00:13:03.679 --> 00:13:05.723
OMURA SECURITIES CO., LTD

00:13:09.226 --> 00:13:13.272
DK Ventures specializes in hostile M&As.

00:13:13.897 --> 00:13:19.111
Guess who was behind almost every
corporate control dispute in Asia

00:13:19.194 --> 00:13:21.614
over the past five years?

00:13:21.697 --> 00:13:22.740
"DK."

00:13:25.993 --> 00:13:29.204
I wonder why you did all that research
when I never asked you to.

00:13:29.288 --> 00:13:32.166
Believe it or not,
I was just as passionate at your age.

00:13:33.125 --> 00:13:35.294
I looked into it out of curiosity,
that's all.

00:13:38.422 --> 00:13:43.135
Their endgame might be to take over
Hanmin Investment & Securities,

00:13:43.218 --> 00:13:47.473
but unless they make a clear move,
we don't have grounds to act.

00:13:47.556 --> 00:13:50.851
I'm sure they're not here
just to take over Hanmin.

00:13:51.935 --> 00:13:54.980
If you think about
why Shin Jung-woo joined Hanmin,

00:13:56.023 --> 00:13:59.735
it's the quickest and easiest way
to get intel on Korean companies.

00:14:02.613 --> 00:14:03.989
That's true, but…

00:14:05.366 --> 00:14:06.325
President Shin

00:14:07.910 --> 00:14:09.495
seemed like a good guy.

00:14:11.288 --> 00:14:12.998
Just hurry up and process my resignation.

00:14:16.835 --> 00:14:19.797
I intended to catch Yehppee
within 100 days and return,

00:14:21.298 --> 00:14:23.258
but I guess I got to know
too many people here.

00:14:27.221 --> 00:14:28.055
Sometimes…

00:14:30.224 --> 00:14:32.434
it feels like Hanmin is my company.

00:14:39.024 --> 00:14:40.025
Hong.

00:14:43.153 --> 00:14:44.405
It's not your fault.

00:14:46.407 --> 00:14:49.535
It's a shame your roommate
made the choice she did,

00:14:50.786 --> 00:14:52.663
but try not to blame yourself too much.

00:14:57.001 --> 00:14:59.670
You said the same thing nine years ago,

00:15:00.587 --> 00:15:01.964
at his funeral.

00:15:10.264 --> 00:15:11.598
It'll be different this time.

00:15:12.641 --> 00:15:13.475
See you.

00:15:19.982 --> 00:15:21.108
Hong.

00:15:21.191 --> 00:15:22.359
Don't ignore my calls!

00:15:23.402 --> 00:15:24.778
Take care of yourself!

00:15:25.362 --> 00:15:27.573
And keep all your receipts!

00:15:30.909 --> 00:15:31.827
Who knows?

00:15:31.910 --> 00:15:34.246
If you return safely,
they might expense them for you.

00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:39.334
Sir!

00:15:40.627 --> 00:15:42.921
Is this man smoking the whole pack?

00:15:46.467 --> 00:15:49.762
Let's look for more Korean firms
that desperately need to secure financing.

00:15:49.845 --> 00:15:51.388
{\an8}ANALYSIS OF INDUSTRY TRENDS
AND MARKET COMPETITIVENESS

00:15:52.097 --> 00:15:53.557
Did you rank them yourself?

00:15:54.391 --> 00:15:55.225
Yeah.

00:15:55.309 --> 00:15:58.020
Category C covers firms
subject to IMF-led restructuring,

00:15:58.103 --> 00:16:01.565
Category B covers firms whose finances
declined sharply due to liquidity issues,

00:16:01.648 --> 00:16:04.526
and Category A covers firms
with weak ownership structures.

00:16:04.610 --> 00:16:06.111
Have the head office cross-check them.

00:16:07.863 --> 00:16:08.697
Okay.

00:16:13.118 --> 00:16:14.495
Coryo Investment & Securities has become

00:16:14.578 --> 00:16:16.747
the first financial institution
to go bankrupt today.

00:16:16.830 --> 00:16:19.333
The long-held belief
that financial institutions are

00:16:19.416 --> 00:16:21.668
"too-big-to-fail" has proven false.

00:16:22.252 --> 00:16:24.838
{\an8}Coryo Investment & Securities
has finally collapsed

00:16:24.922 --> 00:16:28.592
{\an8}after failing to cover
270 billion won in promissory notes

00:16:28.675 --> 00:16:30.219
{\an8}that came due between December 13 and 15.

00:16:30.302 --> 00:16:31.720
The immediate cause was

00:16:31.804 --> 00:16:34.014
its partner banks' refusal
to provide funding

00:16:34.098 --> 00:16:37.768
as they grew increasingly risk-averse
under the IMF program.

00:16:37.851 --> 00:16:40.020
The government convened
an emergency meeting tonight

00:16:40.104 --> 00:16:43.315
to confirm Coryo Investment & Securities'
final insolvency

00:16:43.398 --> 00:16:45.442
by suspending its business operations
starting tomorrow.

00:16:45.526 --> 00:16:47.569
CORYO IS DONE FOR
COULD MY FIRM BE IN TROUBLE TOO?

00:16:47.653 --> 00:16:48.904
RUMORS IN YEOUIDO:
COMPANIES ON THE BRINK OF BANKRUPTCY

00:16:48.987 --> 00:16:50.405
THE RUMOR GOING AROUND TODAY…

00:16:50.489 --> 00:16:53.492
EUNBON CONSTRUCTION, NEX ACE INDUSTRIES,
HOJO TRADING, HEOBONG CONSTRUCTION…

00:16:53.575 --> 00:16:55.452
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

00:16:56.161 --> 00:16:57.037
Come on, Big Al.

00:16:57.830 --> 00:16:59.289
Hasn't Executive Director Oh
told you anything?

00:16:59.373 --> 00:17:02.501
Hanmin was mentioned
in that rumor post on Yeouido Pirates.

00:17:02.584 --> 00:17:03.961
I haven't heard anything.

00:17:04.545 --> 00:17:06.421
Besides, aren't you closer buddies
with my dad?

00:17:06.505 --> 00:17:08.340
Have you joined his side already?

00:17:08.423 --> 00:17:10.050
What are you talking about?

00:17:10.134 --> 00:17:11.969
He's actually pretty hard to befriend…

00:17:12.052 --> 00:17:14.596
My goodness.

00:17:15.097 --> 00:17:17.224
You see, I…

00:17:17.307 --> 00:17:19.101
I respect Executive Director Oh.

00:17:20.227 --> 00:17:22.062
My dad would be pleased to hear that.

00:17:22.896 --> 00:17:26.441
The chairman favoring the president
has him feeling excluded lately.

00:17:26.525 --> 00:17:27.651
I see.

00:17:28.902 --> 00:17:32.281
I wonder if that rumor about the firms
soon to go bankrupt is really true.

00:17:33.490 --> 00:17:34.533
Who started spreading it?

00:17:38.745 --> 00:17:40.372
Where did you even find this?

00:17:40.873 --> 00:17:43.250
I subscribed as soon as I got to Seoul.

00:17:44.168 --> 00:17:45.544
Nobody just reads the newspaper anymore.

00:17:45.627 --> 00:17:48.630
I hear the Yeouido Pirates community
is influential around here,

00:17:49.214 --> 00:17:50.424
but you need an invite to join.

00:18:08.567 --> 00:18:12.029
What happens if Hanmin goes under
before we're ready to go on our end?

00:18:12.613 --> 00:18:14.406
Who do you think started that rumor?

00:18:15.908 --> 00:18:16.909
I did.

00:18:17.576 --> 00:18:20.537
That's how we put
that categorization work to good use.

00:18:20.621 --> 00:18:24.082
It needs to get beaten up out there
for it to accept our hand.

00:18:24.166 --> 00:18:25.500
And you know what happens next.

00:18:25.584 --> 00:18:26.668
Yeah.

00:18:26.752 --> 00:18:29.880
Express intention to invest
and set up a formal meeting.

00:18:31.632 --> 00:18:34.968
It feels like you're working
even harder in your homeland.

00:18:36.720 --> 00:18:40.224
These companies are only useful
for lining the owners' pockets.

00:18:40.307 --> 00:18:42.100
What reason do they have to exist?

00:18:42.184 --> 00:18:44.102
Hanmin is no different.

00:18:44.186 --> 00:18:45.938
They've been lucky for far too long.

00:18:49.524 --> 00:18:53.403
President Shin and the CEO of DK
were talking about that rumor earlier.

00:18:53.904 --> 00:18:56.031
This company might go under
before we even get started.

00:18:57.032 --> 00:18:57.950
It won't just yet.

00:18:59.201 --> 00:19:00.244
How can you be so sure?

00:19:00.327 --> 00:19:01.662
They're all dropping like flies.

00:19:02.246 --> 00:19:03.872
Look at Nora's mama and Al's papa.

00:19:04.498 --> 00:19:06.500
Would they go to such lengths
to inherit a company

