00:35:36.405 --> 00:35:38.824
They felt guilty because it's true.
That's why they shut it down.

00:35:39.700 --> 00:35:41.535
I will never forgive them.

00:35:44.121 --> 00:35:45.665
I get it, but let's eat for now.

00:35:46.165 --> 00:35:47.500
- Okay.
- Okay.

00:35:50.753 --> 00:35:52.797
That Captain definitely knows something.

00:35:57.927 --> 00:36:01.305
{\an8}Yeouido Pirates is back
with a must-read announcement!

00:36:07.144 --> 00:36:08.604
The Captain posted a new announcement!

00:36:12.483 --> 00:36:14.235
"If you keep coming after us,

00:36:14.318 --> 00:36:17.321
we will expose the details
of Hanmin's slush fund."

00:36:18.239 --> 00:36:19.282
The slush fund?

00:36:19.365 --> 00:36:20.241
Hold on.

00:36:20.783 --> 00:36:24.036
"Pildong, general counsel, shell company."

00:36:24.704 --> 00:36:28.124
Pildong was a new law firm
that was established only last November,

00:36:28.958 --> 00:36:31.460
but they ended up
representing Chairman Kang.

00:36:31.544 --> 00:36:32.378
Why?

00:36:32.461 --> 00:36:34.171
Because its senior managing partner

00:36:34.255 --> 00:36:36.507
worked as general counsel
for Hanmin until October.

00:36:36.590 --> 00:36:39.093
Subsequently,
they were appointed as counsel

00:36:39.176 --> 00:36:40.928
for three well-capitalized
shell companies.

00:36:41.012 --> 00:36:44.098
We also suspect Hanmin
to be the source of their funds.

00:36:44.181 --> 00:36:45.391
Wait, I know this.

00:36:45.474 --> 00:36:46.809
This was what I was investigating.

00:36:46.892 --> 00:36:48.019
It's an insider.

00:36:48.644 --> 00:36:51.355
The Captain is someone inside Hanmin.

00:36:52.064 --> 00:36:55.860
What if they have
more up-to-date intel than our ledger?

00:36:58.279 --> 00:36:59.864
We must find them
and get them on our side.

00:37:00.740 --> 00:37:02.783
Because the enemy of my enemy is an ally?

00:37:20.009 --> 00:37:24.305
YEOUIDO PIRATES IS BACK
WITH A MUST-READ ANNOUNCEMENT!

00:37:25.890 --> 00:37:27.892
This "Captain"…

00:37:29.727 --> 00:37:30.895
I wonder what their deal is.

00:37:33.773 --> 00:37:38.069
You see, I checked it out
to monitor the situation,

00:37:38.152 --> 00:37:39.695
and it seems they're very well-informed.

00:37:40.404 --> 00:37:44.033
They might not be bluffing
about exposing our slush fund.

00:37:45.242 --> 00:37:48.037
What if they really do have
cards up their sleeve?

00:37:54.627 --> 00:37:56.462
The slush fund must be
quite a formidable amount.

00:37:57.380 --> 00:38:00.091
Yet you managed to safely avoid
the prosecutors' investigation.

00:38:00.841 --> 00:38:01.842
Well…

00:38:02.593 --> 00:38:04.720
I wouldn't know anything about that.

00:38:04.804 --> 00:38:07.848
Must we work so hard to preserve something
we know nothing about?

00:38:09.683 --> 00:38:10.559
Well…

00:38:11.352 --> 00:38:12.853
The slush fund…

00:38:13.437 --> 00:38:14.814
Ms. Song would know.

00:38:14.897 --> 00:38:16.482
She's always by his side, after all.

00:38:16.565 --> 00:38:17.441
I know nothing.

00:38:18.692 --> 00:38:21.654
First, we must find
the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

00:38:21.737 --> 00:38:23.697
Right, we should.

00:38:23.781 --> 00:38:24.824
We must.

00:38:24.907 --> 00:38:25.741
Mr. Oh.

00:38:26.700 --> 00:38:27.660
I'll leave it to you again.

00:38:28.869 --> 00:38:30.955
Me? Again?

00:38:31.038 --> 00:38:34.208
You've been spearheading
the task up until now,

00:38:34.291 --> 00:38:36.335
so me taking over now would be a bit…

00:38:37.169 --> 00:38:39.213
It would be unideal, right?

00:38:39.296 --> 00:38:40.172
Probably.

00:38:40.256 --> 00:38:42.383
Right. I should handle it.

00:38:43.092 --> 00:38:44.135
- I'll take care of it.
- Yes.

00:38:46.429 --> 00:38:47.930
That jerk.

00:38:52.852 --> 00:38:54.061
Jeez, you scared me.

00:38:54.728 --> 00:38:57.690
Ms. Lee, tell Cha from Research
to come to my office immediately.

00:38:58.274 --> 00:38:59.525
And bring two cups of tea.

00:38:59.608 --> 00:39:00.609
Yes, sir.

00:39:04.822 --> 00:39:08.909
Maybe Executive Director Oh was provoked
by President Shin and Nora's engagement?

00:39:10.244 --> 00:39:12.913
He's become a total henchman
for the president.

00:39:12.997 --> 00:39:14.957
He keeps coming back with updates,

00:39:15.040 --> 00:39:17.751
and the president told him
to find the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

00:39:17.835 --> 00:39:19.044
See? I was right.

00:39:19.670 --> 00:39:21.338
We need to find them first.

00:39:24.258 --> 00:39:25.217
Could the Captain be

00:39:26.010 --> 00:39:27.178
the same person?

00:39:30.890 --> 00:39:34.351
The whistleblower who sent
the slush fund ledger to the president.

00:39:36.103 --> 00:39:38.272
I don't think so, because Yehppee is…

00:39:42.485 --> 00:39:43.486
See?

00:39:43.569 --> 00:39:45.279
You still don't trust me.

00:39:45.362 --> 00:39:48.282
It's not that.
It's just that I need to protect them.

00:39:49.450 --> 00:39:51.869
Well, although they abandoned me and left.

00:39:58.918 --> 00:40:00.044
ACCESS PROHIBITED

00:40:00.127 --> 00:40:01.462
ACCESS PERMITTED

00:40:01.545 --> 00:40:02.588
DISCUSSION BOARD

00:40:02.671 --> 00:40:03.506
Here's a preview.

00:40:03.589 --> 00:40:07.343
These are classified documents from Hanmin
for your reading pleasure.

00:40:07.426 --> 00:40:08.427
Roar.

00:40:08.511 --> 00:40:11.222
PREVIEW: CLASSIFIED DOCUMENTS
FROM HANMIN EXPOSED

00:40:11.805 --> 00:40:14.058
{\an8}INTRANET DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT
IMPROVEMENT PROPOSAL

00:40:17.311 --> 00:40:19.355
We most certainly took care of it.

00:40:19.897 --> 00:40:22.608
But this document was only briefed today.

00:40:22.691 --> 00:40:26.237
It's a classified document
that only an insider would have access to.

00:40:26.320 --> 00:40:29.073
These jerks weren't bluffing.

00:40:30.199 --> 00:40:32.284
Should I report this to President Shin?

00:40:32.368 --> 00:40:34.662
That would only stir up trouble,
don't you think?

00:40:37.289 --> 00:40:38.123
What is it?

00:40:38.958 --> 00:40:40.251
You suspect someone, don't you?

00:40:42.545 --> 00:40:43.921
Well…

00:40:44.004 --> 00:40:45.339
If it wasn't an insider…

00:40:45.422 --> 00:40:46.257
Yes?

00:40:47.341 --> 00:40:50.386
An outsider must have done it?

00:40:55.057 --> 00:40:56.058
Are you saying

00:40:56.141 --> 00:40:58.644
that the whole country is a suspect?

00:41:01.397 --> 00:41:03.524
Perhaps you should consult
the head of the IT Division?

00:41:05.943 --> 00:41:06.777
Data systems.

00:41:07.361 --> 00:41:08.988
- Networks.
- Yes.

00:41:17.997 --> 00:41:20.040
Mr. Lee from the IT Division told me

00:41:20.124 --> 00:41:22.334
that Executive Director Oh
summoned the head of IT

00:41:22.418 --> 00:41:24.753
and asked who could've leaked
the classified document.

00:41:25.254 --> 00:41:28.674
Then he flipped out and ordered him
to see if there were signs of hacking.

00:41:28.757 --> 00:41:30.968
If it were a hacker,
they would've demanded money,

00:41:31.051 --> 00:41:31.927
not played mind games.

00:41:33.137 --> 00:41:35.639
That classified document
was the intranet improvement proposal.

00:41:35.723 --> 00:41:38.392
The president went straight
to Mr. Lee to take care of it,

00:41:38.475 --> 00:41:39.810
bypassing the head of IT.

00:41:40.394 --> 00:41:42.062
Lee Yong-gi produced it,

00:41:42.146 --> 00:41:45.608
and Albert Oh of Trading
and Cha Jung-il of Research were CC-ed.

00:41:45.691 --> 00:41:47.067
Shin Jung-woo was the recipient,

00:41:47.151 --> 00:41:49.403
and I also snuck a peek.

00:41:50.487 --> 00:41:53.240
Only those five people
had access to that document.

00:41:53.324 --> 00:41:56.410
Then those are
our five Captain candidates.

00:41:59.580 --> 00:42:00.414
It's not you, is it?

00:42:01.457 --> 00:42:02.666
Of course it's not me.

00:42:02.750 --> 00:42:04.793
Would I be here if I had such talents?

00:42:05.753 --> 00:42:06.587
What about Shin Jung-woo?

00:42:06.670 --> 00:42:07.921
It's not him, either.

00:42:08.005 --> 00:42:10.007
Yeouido Pirates was created a year ago.

00:42:11.592 --> 00:42:15.346
Mr. Lee was in the breakroom with me
when that post was uploaded,

00:42:15.429 --> 00:42:16.513
so he's ruled out.

00:42:18.098 --> 00:42:19.558
My gut tells me

00:42:19.642 --> 00:42:22.269
that Cha is perfectly capable
of such obnoxious cockiness.

00:42:22.853 --> 00:42:25.898
Gosh, I really hope it's not that jerk.

00:42:30.152 --> 00:42:31.779
Let's try leaking something else.

00:42:39.828 --> 00:42:40.829
Mr. Cha.

00:42:40.913 --> 00:42:42.498
Do you know what happens
when God gets angry?

00:42:44.625 --> 00:42:45.501
He gets cross.

00:42:46.710 --> 00:42:48.712
There are two primary Captain candidates.

00:42:49.463 --> 00:42:51.924
Albert Oh and Cha Jung-il.

00:42:59.973 --> 00:43:01.558
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

00:43:02.309 --> 00:43:03.143
Thank you.

00:43:11.902 --> 00:43:14.613
Make it seem like
it was mixed up at the copier,

00:43:14.697 --> 00:43:16.031
and the bait is cast.

00:43:16.115 --> 00:43:18.492
DOMESTIC SUPPLY AND DEMAND OUTLOOK,
GLOBAL SUPPLY AND DEMAND OUTLOOK

00:43:19.076 --> 00:43:21.161
Hot off the press,

00:43:21.245 --> 00:43:23.789
Hanmin's preliminary budget
for next year unveiled!

00:43:25.833 --> 00:43:27.918
1998 CONTINGENCY BUDGET PLAN

00:43:29.920 --> 00:43:32.840
HANMIN'S PRELIMINARY BUDGET
FOR NEXT YEAR UNVEILED!

00:43:32.923 --> 00:43:36.093
OPERATION COSTS, LABOR COSTS, EXPENSES…

00:43:36.176 --> 00:43:38.178
Do they match up? Do you know who it is?

00:43:39.847 --> 00:43:41.348
This punk…

00:43:49.648 --> 00:43:50.566
Let's get started.

00:44:09.168 --> 00:44:10.669
What are you doing?

00:44:18.802 --> 00:44:20.137
This won't take long.

00:44:20.220 --> 00:44:21.221
Try moving your hands.

00:44:24.016 --> 00:44:25.100
It doesn't hurt, right?

00:44:25.184 --> 00:44:27.102
This is for everyone's safety.

00:44:27.895 --> 00:44:29.688
Everyone in Research is gone for the day,

00:44:29.772 --> 00:44:31.982
and Mr. Lee can't come
because he's busy working overtime

00:44:32.065 --> 00:44:33.442
on the last leak by himself.

00:44:34.943 --> 00:44:37.154
Just do as we say, and you'll be fine.

00:44:41.492 --> 00:44:43.285
This sort of genre isn't my thing.

00:45:02.930 --> 00:45:04.515
I bought those noodles.

00:45:06.934 --> 00:45:08.685
You just need to answer my questions,

00:45:09.394 --> 00:45:11.396
Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

00:45:13.065 --> 00:45:14.775
What? Me?

00:45:14.858 --> 00:45:16.318
I'm the Captain?

00:45:16.401 --> 00:45:18.237
Yes. You.

00:45:19.363 --> 00:45:21.448
You seem overly confident
about that, Ms. Hong.

00:45:23.116 --> 00:45:24.326
How could I not be?

00:45:29.748 --> 00:45:31.959
GLOBAL SUPPLY AND DEMAND OUTLOOK

00:45:34.920 --> 00:45:37.089
1998 CONTINGENCY BUDGET PLAN

00:45:37.172 --> 00:45:38.549
{\an8}Hanmin's confidential documents

00:45:38.632 --> 00:45:40.759
{\an8}were consistently uploaded
to Yeouido Pirates.

00:45:43.011 --> 00:45:44.388
Based on that,

00:45:44.471 --> 00:45:47.558
we leaked next year's budget plan
to you and Mr. Cha Jung-il,

00:45:49.017 --> 00:45:50.978
our two Captain candidates.

00:45:55.190 --> 00:45:56.525
And today,

00:45:56.608 --> 00:46:01.905
a post appeared on Yeouido Pirates
with Hanmin's budget plan for next year.

00:46:01.989 --> 00:46:05.325
Sure. I think I saw
a budget plan or whatever.

00:46:05.409 --> 00:46:06.827
But I don't know how to read that.

00:46:06.910 --> 00:46:08.370
And why just me?

00:46:08.453 --> 00:46:10.747
Based on that logic,
Mr. Cha should be tied up next to me.

00:46:11.707 --> 00:46:14.459
Because you were the one
who uploaded today's post.

00:46:14.543 --> 00:46:16.920
No, I didn't. I swear it wasn't me!

00:46:18.005 --> 00:46:19.381
It is you.

00:46:20.799 --> 00:46:22.926
We gave different reports to each suspect.

00:46:23.927 --> 00:46:25.971
The new post on Yeouido Pirates

00:46:26.054 --> 00:46:28.932
contained information
that was leaked to you alone.

00:46:29.016 --> 00:46:30.809
The numbers were different, you see.

00:46:34.855 --> 00:46:38.609
Come to think of it,
I was able to join Yeouido Pirates

00:46:39.401 --> 00:46:40.736
with your referral.

00:46:41.320 --> 00:46:42.195
Remember?

00:46:43.363 --> 00:46:44.740
Why didn't you ask me?

00:46:45.949 --> 00:46:47.826
- Pardon?
- For an invite to the Yeouido Pirates.

00:46:48.535 --> 00:46:49.411
I can do that for you.

00:46:54.458 --> 00:46:55.417
Really?

00:46:58.211 --> 00:46:59.171
You're right.

00:47:01.214 --> 00:47:02.966
I am the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

00:47:03.842 --> 00:47:04.676
Oh my.

00:47:05.385 --> 00:47:07.012
Why would the chairman's grandson
do such a thing?

00:47:07.095 --> 00:47:09.181
That's what I'd like to ask you two.

00:47:09.264 --> 00:47:11.725
Why would you two do something like this?

00:47:20.734 --> 00:47:22.527
Big Al. It's me, Yong-gi.

00:47:23.236 --> 00:47:24.696
You're in there, right?

00:47:24.780 --> 00:47:26.073
Let him in.

00:47:27.240 --> 00:47:28.909
He's my one and only crew member.

00:47:30.118 --> 00:47:31.662
Mr. Lee is a crew member?

00:47:33.163 --> 00:47:34.289
You two are accomplices?

00:47:51.932 --> 00:47:55.769
My dad found out I was in film school,
and he forced me to return to Korea.

00:48:01.066 --> 00:48:03.944
Watching movies all day
eventually got old.

00:48:09.157 --> 00:48:11.326
It felt like I'd been exiled
to an island called Yeouido.

00:48:13.787 --> 00:48:15.914
But some people around me
loved their jobs,

00:48:15.997 --> 00:48:17.791
like Uncle Myeong-hwi.

00:48:19.334 --> 00:48:21.628
I guess I wanted
to do something worthwhile.

00:48:24.131 --> 00:48:26.508
That's when Mr. Lee caught my eye.

00:48:27.843 --> 00:48:30.387
He was a genius hacker geek,
clearly ahead of his time.

00:48:31.972 --> 00:48:35.308
And I picked up top-tier insider intel
at home and at work.

00:48:35.851 --> 00:48:38.145
Since Mr. Lee was serious
about his cyber world,

00:48:38.228 --> 00:48:39.604
I proposed working together.

00:48:48.321 --> 00:48:49.448
{\an8}OPERATION COMPLETE!

00:48:51.825 --> 00:48:52.784
YEOUIDO PIRATES

00:48:52.868 --> 00:48:56.246
- Is it done?
- Now, this is the main page.

00:48:57.581 --> 00:49:00.208
Try writing a post or something.

00:49:00.292 --> 00:49:01.209
- A post.
- Yeah.

00:49:02.586 --> 00:49:05.088
Let's enter the discussion board…

00:49:05.922 --> 00:49:07.090
We need a title.

00:49:08.383 --> 00:49:09.468
"It's finally here."

00:49:10.761 --> 00:49:14.473
"Introducing Yeouido Pirates,
the complete intel collection of Yeouido."

00:49:14.973 --> 00:49:15.974
DISCUSSION BOARD

00:49:16.641 --> 00:49:20.645
"We look forward to a vibrant
and active community of members."

00:49:20.729 --> 00:49:22.063
PUBLISH

00:49:24.733 --> 00:49:25.567
Ta-da.

00:49:27.444 --> 00:49:28.320
It's done.

00:49:29.362 --> 00:49:31.031
- It's up.
- Wow, this is…

00:49:31.114 --> 00:49:32.407
We did it.

00:49:34.326 --> 00:49:35.952
You're the Captain now.

00:49:40.916 --> 00:49:44.669
Here, the members
can freely post whatever they wish.

00:49:48.840 --> 00:49:50.675
How did Big Al convince you?

00:49:52.677 --> 00:49:55.263
"Let's become a band of pirates
that sails the sea of information."

00:49:55.347 --> 00:49:57.641
"Let's democratize access
to monopolized information."

00:49:58.141 --> 00:50:00.143
"Let's make a world
where the people of Yeouido

00:50:00.227 --> 00:50:02.103
can call a spade a spade without fear."

00:50:07.150 --> 00:50:08.652
How grandiose.

00:50:09.319 --> 00:50:12.030
There was a reason
why you two were attached at the hip.

00:50:12.531 --> 00:50:15.951
That's why you met up here after work,
even after the restructuring.

00:50:16.535 --> 00:50:18.161
Why are you digging into Yeouido Pirates?

00:50:19.329 --> 00:50:20.455
Did Ms. Song put you up to it?

00:50:21.581 --> 00:50:22.833
Maybe my dad?

00:50:22.916 --> 00:50:25.085
Or maybe President Shin?

00:50:25.168 --> 00:50:27.587
As if we'd tie someone up
because someone ordered us to.

00:50:28.171 --> 00:50:30.257
Then why are you doing this?

00:50:30.340 --> 00:50:34.219
President Shin and Executive Director Oh
are looking for the Captain.

00:50:34.302 --> 00:50:37.264
We found you first before things got ugly.

00:50:37.347 --> 00:50:38.515
Why?

00:50:40.600 --> 00:50:42.102
We're hoping to make a deal.

00:50:42.602 --> 00:50:44.437
You said in a post on Yeouido Pirates

00:50:45.438 --> 00:50:47.524
that you'd expose the slush fund
if provoked further.

00:50:50.944 --> 00:50:52.112
What's this now?

00:50:52.195 --> 00:50:54.114
What's with that sigh?

00:50:54.197 --> 00:50:56.074
Regarding the slush fund's size
and whereabouts…

00:50:58.451 --> 00:50:59.286
we know nothing.

00:51:00.620 --> 00:51:03.331
We just reworked what Uncle Myeong-hwi
let slip when he was drunk.

00:51:03.415 --> 00:51:05.542
They kept coming after us,
so we swung big.

00:51:06.751 --> 00:51:08.837
Can you untie me now?

00:51:10.714 --> 00:51:12.132
Untie me!

00:51:22.017 --> 00:51:25.478
They wouldn't tell on us, would they?

00:51:26.146 --> 00:51:27.981
Who would they tell, and about what?

00:51:28.064 --> 00:51:29.357
We asked about the slush fund.

00:51:30.233 --> 00:51:31.860
But nothing about stealing it, right?

00:51:32.611 --> 00:51:35.447
If anything, they're the ones
shaking in their boots.

00:51:41.995 --> 00:51:44.956
Ms. Hong and Ms. Go
wouldn't tell on us, right?

00:51:45.540 --> 00:51:46.750
Of course not.

00:51:46.833 --> 00:51:49.169
Then why did they ask
about the slush fund?

00:52:01.473 --> 00:52:04.017
I'll go back and ask Ms. Hong about it.

00:52:04.100 --> 00:52:05.060
No, don't.

00:52:05.602 --> 00:52:06.770
Go home. I'll see you tomorrow.

00:52:08.021 --> 00:52:08.855
Okay.

00:52:10.398 --> 00:52:11.358
Have a good night.

00:52:47.852 --> 00:52:48.895
It's been a while,

00:52:48.979 --> 00:52:50.105
Mr. Auto Repair Shop.

00:53:05.537 --> 00:53:06.538
That hurts.

00:53:06.997 --> 00:53:09.582
Let's talk this out, all right?

00:53:09.666 --> 00:53:11.459
At least tell me what you want.

00:53:16.131 --> 00:53:17.007
Hong Keum-bo.

00:53:17.549 --> 00:53:18.383
Hong Keum-bo?

00:53:18.466 --> 00:53:20.343
The woman you came with
to my auto repair shop.

00:53:20.427 --> 00:53:22.220
Just tell me how you know her.

00:53:34.941 --> 00:53:38.236
Do you think I could go
to a birthday party I wasn't invited to?

00:53:38.319 --> 00:53:41.197
To be precise,
another friend did invite me.

00:53:41.281 --> 00:53:42.574
When's their birthday?

00:53:42.657 --> 00:53:44.868
It's December 24th, on Christmas Eve.

00:53:46.536 --> 00:53:49.289
Is it your former roommate's birthday?

00:53:49.956 --> 00:53:51.166
How did you know?

00:53:53.209 --> 00:53:56.046
You mentioned you didn't have
many friends in Seoul.

00:53:58.048 --> 00:54:00.717
You remembered that?

00:54:02.427 --> 00:54:03.511
Yes, well…

00:54:04.512 --> 00:54:06.723
I would've forgotten
if it hadn't been a special day,

00:54:07.307 --> 00:54:09.976
but someone I dated long ago
was also born on December 24th.

00:54:11.686 --> 00:54:13.563
Whenever Christmas carols
played in the streets,

00:54:13.646 --> 00:54:16.107
she'd say it was like
a preview of her birthday.

00:54:28.745 --> 00:54:31.164
Let's help the less fortunate!

00:54:33.917 --> 00:54:36.294
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:54:36.377 --> 00:54:38.213
- Merry Christmas.
- Thank you.

00:54:38.296 --> 00:54:39.798
- Take care.
- Goodbye.

00:54:39.881 --> 00:54:42.217
- A sleighing song tonight
- A sleighing song tonight

