{\an8}ULLALA CHICKEN

00:55:17.877 --> 00:55:20.755
Ma'am, this is
way too much food for just us.

00:55:20.839 --> 00:55:22.298
Not at all.

00:55:23.967 --> 00:55:25.802
- Take the leftovers home.
- Okay.

00:55:25.885 --> 00:55:28.221
Honey, you packed the kimchi
and ginseng chicken soup, right?

00:55:28.304 --> 00:55:30.557
Of course I did.

00:55:30.640 --> 00:55:33.977
Bom, Grandma and I are going
to the nursing home to volunteer,

00:55:34.060 --> 00:55:35.603
so have fun with your aunties, okay?

00:55:35.687 --> 00:55:36.604
Okay!

00:55:40.275 --> 00:55:41.442
Auntie!

00:55:48.283 --> 00:55:50.118
Let me check your invitations.

00:55:55.039 --> 00:55:58.418
HONG KEUM-BO'S
BIRTHDAY PARTY INVITATION

00:56:06.426 --> 00:56:07.552
Here you go.

00:56:07.635 --> 00:56:09.179
Thank you!

00:56:09.262 --> 00:56:10.138
It's Christmas Eve.

00:56:10.847 --> 00:56:12.307
Don't you have a date with the president?

00:56:12.390 --> 00:56:14.225
He said he had important plans today.

00:56:15.059 --> 00:56:16.686
That's suspicious.

00:56:16.769 --> 00:56:18.855
Could he have another woman?

00:56:19.647 --> 00:56:23.443
You know, like his first love,
an ex-girlfriend, or a secret lover?

00:56:24.444 --> 00:56:25.278
And what if

00:56:26.237 --> 00:56:27.739
she's someone we know?

00:56:33.244 --> 00:56:34.871
Someone at the president's level…

00:56:35.872 --> 00:56:37.248
would probably date an actress, right?

00:56:38.666 --> 00:56:39.792
Maybe Shim Eun-ha from The Last Match?

00:56:39.876 --> 00:56:41.336
Or Kim Hee-seon from Propose?

00:56:42.795 --> 00:56:44.714
Jeez, I'm just kidding.

00:56:45.673 --> 00:56:47.759
How many candles do you want? All 35?

00:56:48.509 --> 00:56:49.928
Just one.

00:56:50.595 --> 00:56:52.764
Is it her first birthday or something?
Right, Bom?

00:56:57.393 --> 00:56:59.312
Sure, it's not like it costs extra.

00:57:02.690 --> 00:57:03.608
Pink?

00:57:12.075 --> 00:57:13.117
Okay.

00:57:13.201 --> 00:57:16.287
- Happy birthday to you
- Happy birthday to you

00:57:16.371 --> 00:57:19.290
- Happy birthday to you
- Happy birthday to you

00:57:19.374 --> 00:57:21.793
- Happy birthday, dear Ms. Hong
- Happy birthday

00:57:21.876 --> 00:57:23.670
- Dear Hong Keum-bo
- Dear Auntie Jang-mi

00:57:23.753 --> 00:57:27.048
- Happy birthday to you
- Happy birthday to you

00:57:34.681 --> 00:57:35.515
Good job.

00:57:38.893 --> 00:57:39.894
Ta-da!

00:57:40.436 --> 00:57:42.313
I wanted us to watch it together.

00:57:42.397 --> 00:57:45.191
They're videos I took
when we were living in the dorms.

00:58:12.927 --> 00:58:14.012
Did you buy that camcorder?

00:58:14.512 --> 00:58:15.805
It looks really expensive.

00:58:17.348 --> 00:58:18.558
Jang-mi!

00:58:19.642 --> 00:58:20.893
What are you doing?

00:58:24.480 --> 00:58:25.481
Cucumber.

00:58:25.565 --> 00:58:27.483
- Cucumber.
- Cucumber.

00:58:30.528 --> 00:58:31.988
Congratulations!

00:58:37.702 --> 00:58:38.870
Have some. It's good.

00:58:40.622 --> 00:58:41.581
Is it good?

00:58:42.999 --> 00:58:44.167
It's so sour.

00:58:44.959 --> 00:58:47.045
- Ta-da.
- Can you do it?

00:58:54.761 --> 00:58:56.387
- Smile.
- Smile.

00:59:00.600 --> 00:59:02.769
Look over here, Bom. Isn't that so cool?

00:59:03.269 --> 00:59:04.646
Look at that!

00:59:07.774 --> 00:59:08.691
It's not easy.

00:59:08.775 --> 00:59:11.486
You broke it!

00:59:11.569 --> 00:59:14.364
It's okay. It's nothing to cry about.

00:59:14.906 --> 00:59:15.948
Sorry.

00:59:16.532 --> 00:59:19.535
My goodness. Should we try again, Bom?

00:59:19.619 --> 00:59:21.287
Do you want a taste?

00:59:21.371 --> 00:59:23.998
Isn't it so good?

00:59:24.624 --> 00:59:25.833
It's good, isn't it?

00:59:27.168 --> 00:59:28.127
Let's have some more.

00:59:30.838 --> 00:59:33.508
Hey, turn on the TV or play some music.

00:59:34.842 --> 00:59:36.010
Let's play some Christmas carols.

00:59:38.513 --> 00:59:39.347
I'm in.

00:59:39.430 --> 00:59:41.516
Whenever Christmas carols
play in the streets,

00:59:41.599 --> 00:59:43.476
it's like a preview of my birthday.

00:59:45.603 --> 00:59:48.523
Someone I dated long ago
was also born on December 24th.

00:59:49.857 --> 00:59:51.567
Whenever Christmas carols
played in the streets,

00:59:52.151 --> 00:59:54.320
she'd say it was like
a preview of her birthday.

00:59:58.908 --> 01:00:00.118
We're closed today.

01:00:15.800 --> 01:00:16.884
It's so cold.

01:00:19.887 --> 01:00:21.764
What happened to your lips?

01:00:25.435 --> 01:00:27.353
How did you know about my parents' place?

01:00:27.437 --> 01:00:29.897
Wait, are you here to pick up your aunt?

01:00:29.981 --> 01:00:32.358
Aunt Nora and I aren't even that close.

01:00:34.110 --> 01:00:36.237
But you two are much closer
than I expected.

01:00:37.947 --> 01:00:39.323
We're not that close.

01:00:43.411 --> 01:00:44.746
You didn't tell anyone, did you?

01:00:46.205 --> 01:00:48.416
That I'm the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

01:00:49.792 --> 01:00:50.835
I didn't.

01:00:51.627 --> 01:00:53.379
Then I'll keep your secret too.

01:00:55.465 --> 01:00:57.508
Inspector of the Capital Market
Investigation Division at the FSS…

01:00:59.719 --> 01:01:00.970
Hong Keum-bo.

01:01:16.027 --> 01:01:17.069
When did you find out?

01:01:18.279 --> 01:01:20.072
It doesn't seem like
you feigned ignorance.

01:01:20.656 --> 01:01:21.866
Remember Horang Auto Repair Shop?

01:01:23.326 --> 01:01:25.286
A few days ago, I ran into that scary man

01:01:25.912 --> 01:01:27.205
in front of our office building.

01:01:28.998 --> 01:01:30.374
He asked about Hong Keum-bo.

01:01:33.711 --> 01:01:34.754
Hong Keum-bo.

01:01:35.671 --> 01:01:36.506
Hong Keum-bo?

01:01:36.589 --> 01:01:38.466
The woman you came with
to my auto repair shop.

01:01:39.842 --> 01:01:41.427
Just tell me how you know her.

01:01:54.023 --> 01:01:55.900
Fine, I'll tell you!

01:01:55.983 --> 01:01:56.859
I will tell you!

01:02:00.279 --> 01:02:01.447
That pretty highway ghost?

01:02:02.365 --> 01:02:03.574
I haven't seen her since.

01:02:04.784 --> 01:02:06.369
I'm telling you the truth!

01:02:06.953 --> 01:02:08.246
She told me to just go home

01:02:08.329 --> 01:02:10.498
if I didn't want to get beaten up
in some random place!

01:02:10.581 --> 01:02:11.666
Sir.

01:02:16.420 --> 01:02:18.089
Damn it, that seriously hurts.

01:02:18.589 --> 01:02:20.299
Why are you so violent?

01:02:21.217 --> 01:02:22.760
He says he doesn't know her.

01:02:25.721 --> 01:02:28.432
Hong Keum-bo might've acted alone.

01:02:31.143 --> 01:02:32.854
What should I do with the boy?

01:02:32.937 --> 01:02:34.522
Let Albert go for now.

01:02:51.372 --> 01:02:52.373
Hong Keum-bo.

01:02:55.459 --> 01:02:56.544
"HONG KEUM-BO" SEARCH RESULTS

01:02:58.629 --> 01:03:01.465
{\an8}HONG KEUM-BO, THE FSS WITCH OF YEOUIDO…

01:03:03.342 --> 01:03:04.635
SHE LOOKED INTO HANMIN'S SLUSH FUND…

01:03:04.719 --> 01:03:07.054
"Hanmin's slush fund"?

01:03:07.847 --> 01:03:09.682
You said in a post on Yeouido Pirates

01:03:10.683 --> 01:03:12.768
that you'd expose the slush fund
if provoked further.

01:03:12.852 --> 01:03:14.770
Regarding the slush fund's size
and whereabouts…

01:03:15.646 --> 01:03:16.480
we know nothing.

01:03:26.866 --> 01:03:28.242
I'm looking for someone,

01:03:28.326 --> 01:03:30.745
and I need a clear picture of her face.

01:03:51.474 --> 01:03:53.017
1989 FSS NEW HIRE TRAINING CENTER

01:03:58.481 --> 01:03:59.857
After Uncle Myeong-hwi's accident,

01:04:00.441 --> 01:04:03.903
I once overheard Ms. Song
and my grandfather talking.

01:04:04.487 --> 01:04:07.281
And the demoted FSS inspector
they mentioned then

01:04:08.741 --> 01:04:10.326
lied to get a job in my division?

01:04:12.745 --> 01:04:15.206
Did you tie me to a chair
and ask about the slush fund

01:04:15.289 --> 01:04:16.540
as part of your undercover operation?

01:04:17.959 --> 01:04:18.793
That's right.

01:04:19.377 --> 01:04:20.753
I was doing my job the whole time.

01:04:24.382 --> 01:04:26.467
It's too dangerous for you
to continue working at Hanmin.

01:04:28.552 --> 01:04:30.888
Danger and disappointment
can't be reasons for me to give up.

01:04:32.306 --> 01:04:33.849
There's a job I must finish.

01:04:36.936 --> 01:04:39.063
I knew Hong Keum-bo
wouldn't listen, either.

01:04:42.441 --> 01:04:44.235
I'm not sure if you'd accept this deal,

01:04:45.277 --> 01:04:48.698
but you can't be exposed
as the Captain of Yeouido Pirates either.

01:04:50.449 --> 01:04:52.118
Forget being the successor,

01:04:52.201 --> 01:04:53.703
you'd be disowned.

01:04:55.538 --> 01:04:56.956
So how about we both feign ignorance?

01:04:58.332 --> 01:05:00.001
I don't want to feign ignorance.

01:05:00.084 --> 01:05:01.293
I still think

01:05:02.128 --> 01:05:04.213
we're on the same team.

01:05:08.551 --> 01:05:10.052
Don't you need me for your operation?

01:05:11.303 --> 01:05:12.596
Of course, it won't be for free.

01:05:14.515 --> 01:05:16.225
Do you even know what I'm after?

01:05:17.852 --> 01:05:20.229
Would you be willing to turn over
your entire share in Hanmin

01:05:20.813 --> 01:05:22.106
to me?

01:05:24.900 --> 01:05:25.735
If you'd like.

01:05:26.318 --> 01:05:27.194
In return,

01:05:28.112 --> 01:05:30.740
I need to find the culprit who instigated
Uncle Myeong-hwi's accident.

01:06:09.987 --> 01:06:13.574
A lady invites you to dinner,
and you bring toilet paper?

01:06:13.657 --> 01:06:16.077
It's the best housewarming gift.

01:06:17.787 --> 01:06:20.664
Also, the Ms. Hong I know
is incredibly practical.

01:06:22.958 --> 01:06:24.794
We should've asked Mr. Bang to join.

01:06:28.881 --> 01:06:30.549
He wouldn't be able to handle the truth.

01:06:32.301 --> 01:06:33.135
What truth?

01:06:34.970 --> 01:06:36.013
Mr. Lee.

01:06:37.139 --> 01:06:38.182
Take a deep breath with me.

01:06:38.724 --> 01:06:39.558
Inhale deeply.

01:06:40.684 --> 01:06:41.727
Exhale deeply.

01:06:44.021 --> 01:06:45.314
{\an8}1989 FSS NEW HIRE TRAINING CENTER

01:06:48.651 --> 01:06:49.944
You're with the FSS?

01:06:50.486 --> 01:06:52.446
I resigned, so not anymore.

01:06:53.322 --> 01:06:54.490
And you're older…

01:06:54.573 --> 01:06:55.741
Yes, she is.

01:06:58.536 --> 01:07:00.830
Mr. Lee, you look like
you have a lot of questions.

01:07:01.413 --> 01:07:03.332
I do, but I can wait.

01:07:03.415 --> 01:07:04.291
Just come and sit.

01:07:10.965 --> 01:07:12.842
I'll get right to the point.

01:07:12.925 --> 01:07:15.553
This is what Uncle Myeong-hwi compiled
to blow the whistle with…

01:07:15.636 --> 01:07:17.054
It's the slush fund ledger.

01:07:17.138 --> 01:07:19.557
The FSS does not want to investigate,

01:07:19.640 --> 01:07:22.143
and Hanmin is being targeted
by both internal and external forces.

01:07:22.226 --> 01:07:23.769
You mean DK Ventures and President Shin?

01:07:24.353 --> 01:07:25.563
We figured out as much.

01:07:26.063 --> 01:07:28.732
Our ultimate goal is to
steal the slush fund, buy up the stock,

01:07:28.816 --> 01:07:31.318
and become the major shareholder
to protect the company.

01:07:35.906 --> 01:07:38.534
Our first target is
the domestic slush funds.

01:07:40.035 --> 01:07:40.870
Who manages them?

01:07:46.417 --> 01:07:47.418
DOMESTIC SLUSH FUNDS

01:07:47.501 --> 01:07:49.253
{\an8}"Managed by Executive Director
Oh Deok-gyu?"

01:07:50.754 --> 01:07:51.589
My dad?

01:08:34.298 --> 01:08:36.133
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

01:08:36.842 --> 01:08:38.802
{\an8}You keep so many secrets from me, Dad.

01:08:39.470 --> 01:08:41.430
{\an8}If I become the successor,
it won't be an issue.

01:08:41.972 --> 01:08:43.766
{\an8}Have you heard of the old banknote scam?

01:08:44.266 --> 01:08:47.353
{\an8}- Hong!
- I need the rumor to spread like wildfire.

01:08:47.436 --> 01:08:49.438
{\an8}This must stay between us.

01:08:49.939 --> 01:08:52.358
{\an8}Why take such a big gamble, Big Al?

01:08:52.441 --> 01:08:54.318
{\an8}How can we know you're serious?

01:08:54.401 --> 01:08:55.778
{\an8}Do you know who I am, punk?

01:08:56.695 --> 01:08:59.448
{\an8}Reality is definitely different
from what I anticipated.

01:09:00.199 --> 01:09:01.617
{\an8}Let's go for it. Let's do it.

01:09:01.700 --> 01:09:02.993
{\an8}This is Song Ju-ran.

01:09:03.077 --> 01:09:04.411
{\an8}Can you check on something for me?

01:09:05.120 --> 01:09:05.955
{\an8}Let's get started.

01:09:08.165 --> 01:09:13.170
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim